    {
      "id": "PopularPost74627",
      "post_content": "@Mathx2: Sweet Gygax, you're right! That's brilliant. Probably explains why the zombie doesn't seems nearly as frightened as the fleeing woman.\n  \n   \nAnyway, not as combo-tastic as [Squee, Goblin Nabob](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Squee, Goblin Nabob), but it's recurrsion must be fuel for some low-end casual Johnny tactic. Anybody have any thoughts? It's considerably awkward since it's a from-play trigger, but I have the lingering suspicion that there must be something.\n  \n   \nOther than combos, other zombies are generally better than this guy, as he has the nasty habit of locking down your draw, given the chance. Other zombies just interact favourably with your graveyard (except for the surprisingly large proportion that don't- [Rotting Giant](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rotting Giant), I'm looking at you) without forcing you to play around the possibly repeated loss of your draw.",
      "posted_by": "DoctorKenneth",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost74627\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">@Mathx2: Sweet Gygax, you're right! That's brilliant. Probably explains why the zombie doesn't seems nearly as frightened as the fleeing woman.\r<br/> <br/>Anyway, not as combo-tastic as <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Squee, Goblin Nabob\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Squee, Goblin Nabob\">Squee, Goblin Nabob</a>, but it's recurrsion must be fuel for some low-end casual Johnny tactic. Anybody have any thoughts? It's considerably awkward since it's a from-play trigger, but I have the lingering suspicion that there must be something.\r<br/> <br/>Other than combos, other zombies are generally better than this guy, as he has the nasty habit of locking down your draw, given the chance. Other zombies just interact favourably with your graveyard (except for the surprisingly large proportion that don't- <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Rotting Giant\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rotting Giant\">Rotting Giant</a>, I'm looking at you) without forcing you to play around the possibly repeated loss of your draw.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '74627'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy1392\">DoctorKe